>
  <h1>Editorial Standards</h1>
  <p>
    Our methodology prioritizes transparent assumptions, practical execution context, and
    clear educational scope for US commercial multifamily financing content.
  </p>

  <h2>Scope standards</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Coverage is limited to US multifamily financing for properties with five or more units.</li>
    <li>Articles are educational and do not constitute legal, tax, accounting, or lending advice.</li>
    <li>We avoid unsupported claims and highlight uncertainty where assumptions may vary.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Content development standards</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Each guide must define business-plan assumptions and downside risk context.</li>
    <li>We distinguish in-place performance from stabilized projections in underwriting discussion.</li>
    <li>Comparisons emphasize full-cycle execution trade-offs, not headline pricing alone.</li>
    <li>Market pages present directional context and encourage transaction-level verification.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Review and update process</h2>
  <p>
    Content is periodically reviewed for relevance and clarity as market conditions change.
    We update assumptions, terminology, and examples when needed to keep guidance practical.
    Time-sensitive topics are reflected through update dates and refreshed article notes.
  </p>

  <h2>Source and transparency policy</h2>
  <p>
    We aim to make assumptions explicit, identify where lender practices vary, and avoid
    presenting directional ranges as guaranteed outcomes. Readers should confirm final terms
    directly with qualified lenders and advisors.
  </p>

  <h2>Conflict and compensation disclosure</h2>
  <p>
    Multi-Family USA may receive compensation from lender partners when funded transactions
    occur, but compensation does not determine methodology, calculator logic, or editorial framing.
  </p>
</BasicLayout>
